{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Esports Analytics: Counter-Strike Match Round Predictive Pipeline\n",
    "### End-to-End Predictive Modeling Infrastructure | Candidate Portfolio Asset\n",
    "**Author:** Subhankar  \n",
    "**Objective:** Build, evaluate, and diagnose a dual-model classification workflow to predict real-time round outcomes using high-density telemetry snapshots.\n",
    "\n",
    "---"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. Environment Setup & Library Diagnostics\n",
    "Here we load the necessary software libraries for data structures, matrix operations, modeling, and statistical graphics generation."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import os\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import seaborn as sns\n",
    "from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split\n",
    "from sklearn.preprocessing import LabelEncoder, StandardScaler\n",
    "from sklearn.discriminant_analysis import LinearDiscriminantAnalysis\n",
    "from sklearn.linear_model import LogisticRegression\n",
    "from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestClassifier\n",
    "from sklearn.metrics import accuracy_score, classification_report, confusion_matrix\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Libraries successfully initialized. Ready for ingestion pipeline.\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2. Data Ingestion & Sanitization\n",
    "We ingest our raw CSV telemetry snapshots. To prevent standard Python execution warnings, we flag `low_memory=False` and execute a clean-in-place operation on missing or sparse row segments."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Use raw string formatting to avoid Windows backslash escapes\n",
    "DATA_PATH = r\"D:\\Data Analytics Project\\csgo_round_snapshots.csv\"\n",
    "\n",
    "df = pd.read_csv(DATA_PATH, low_memory=False)\n",
    "print(f\"Dataset successfully loaded. Shape: {df.shape[0]} rows, {df.shape[1]} columns.\")\n",
    "    \n",
    "# Review any sparse entries\n",
    "null_counts = df.isnull().sum().sum()\n",
    "print(f\"Total missing cell items identified: {null_counts}\")\n",
    "    \n",
    "# Enforce safe cleanup\n",
    "df.dropna(inplace=True)\n",
    "print(f\"Sanitization complete. Final record pool count: {df.shape[0]}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3. Exploratory Data Analysis & Target Balance\n",
    "Before initializing models, we generate a class count plot to confirm our target labels are balanced and free from severe skew bias."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "plt.figure(figsize=(6, 4))\n",
    "sns.countplot(x='round_winner', data=df, palette='viridis')\n",
    "plt.title('Target Distribution: Round Winner Class Balance')\n",
    "plt.xlabel('Winning Faction')\n",
    "plt.ylabel('Snapshot Count')\n",
    "plt.show()\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Class Proportions:\")\n",
    "print(df['round_winner'].value_counts(normalize=True))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 4. Feature Engineering & Categorical Encoding\n",
    "We isolate columns by tracking variances and transforming non-numeric data fields like the text-based `map` configurations and our `round_winner` target label via categorical transformations."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Safe copy separation\n",
    "processed_df = df.copy()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Encode the map category\n",
    "le_map = LabelEncoder()\n",
    "processed_df['map'] = le_map.fit_transform(processed_df['map'])\n",
    "\n",
    "# Encode the target label\n",
    "le_winner = LabelEncoder()\n",
    "processed_df['round_winner'] = le_winner.fit_transform(processed_df['round_winner'])\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Encoding mapping complete.\")\n",
    "print(\"Classes labeled:\", dict(zip(le_winner.classes_, le_winner.transform(le_winner.classes_))))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 5. Train-Test Splitting & Data-Safe Feature Scaling\n",
    "To avoid severe feature variance distortions and fully protect against data leakage, we execute our split first, then match our standard scaler rules purely to our training rows."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Separate features and target array\n",
    "X = processed_df.drop(columns=['round_winner'])\n",
    "y = processed_df['round_winner']\n",
    "\n",
    "# Split dataset using a fixed random state for reproducibility\n",
    "X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(X, y, test_size=0.20, random_state=42, stratify=y)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Apply Standard Scaling directly after train-test split to avoid leakage\n",
    "scaler = StandardScaler()\n",
    "X_train_scaled = scaler.fit_transform(X_train)\n",
    "X_test_scaled = scaler.transform(X_test)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Training set shape: {X_train_scaled.shape}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Testing set shape: {X_test_scaled.shape}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 6. Model Training, Optimization & Evaluation\n",
    "We implement Linear Discriminant Analysis (LDA) and an optimized Logistic Regression as our baseline classifiers, followed by a Random Forest Ensemble to handle non-linear weapon-to-economy pairings."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# ---- 1. Linear Discriminant Analysis ----\n",
    "lda_model = LinearDiscriminantAnalysis()\n",
    "lda_model.fit(X_train_scaled, y_train)\n",
    "lda_pred = lda_model.predict(X_test_scaled)\n",
    "\n",
    "# ---- 2. Optimized Logistic Regression (Fixed Convergence) ----\n",
    "log_model = LogisticRegression(max_iter=1000, random_state=42)\n",
    "log_model.fit(X_train_scaled, y_train)\n",
    "log_pred = log_model.predict(X_test_scaled)\n",
    "\n",
    "# ---- 3. Random Forest Ensemble Classifier ----\n",
    "rf_model = RandomForestClassifier(n_estimators=100, random_state=42, n_jobs=-1)\n",
    "rf_model.fit(X_train_scaled, y_train)\n",
    "rf_pred = rf_model.predict(X_test_scaled)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Model evaluations:\")\n",
    "print(f\"LDA Baseline Accuracy         : {accuracy_score(y_test, lda_pred):.4f}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Logistic Regression Accuracy  : {accuracy_score(y_test, log_pred):.4f}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Random Forest Accuracy        : {accuracy_score(y_test, rf_pred):.4f}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 7. Granular Diagnostics & Performance Visualizations\n",
    "We map out a comprehensive classification asset report and plot the top game telemetry metrics derived from our Linear Discriminant Analysis weights."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "print(\"=== Random Forest Deep Diagnostic Asset Report ===\")\n",
    "print(classification_report(y_test, rf_pred, target_names=le_winner.classes_))\n",
    "\n",
    "# Structural Feature Importance extraction from LDA weights\n",
    "importance_scores = np.exp(np.abs(lda_model.coef_)).flatten()\n",
    "feature_importance_df = pd.DataFrame({\n",
    "    'Feature': X.columns,\n",
    "    'Importance_Score': importance_scores\n}).sort_values(by='Importance_Score', ascending=False)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Chart Top 15 telemetric determinants\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))\n",
    "sns.barplot(x='Importance_Score', y='Feature', data=feature_importance_df.head(15), palette='plasma')\n",
    "plt.title('Top 15 Most Influential Features Predicting Round Outcomes (LDA Spaces)', fontsize=12, fontweight='bold')\n",
    "plt.xlabel('Relative Importance Score (Exp of Abs Coefficients)')\n",
    "plt.ylabel('Telemetry Feature Name')\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 8. Portfolio Summary & Key Outcomes\n",
    "* **Operational Gain Matrix:** Transitioning data features out of standard linear spaces (LDA Base ~74.63%) into deep tree rulesets (Random Forest Ensemble) expanded our structural outcome classification accuracy to **~87.73%**.\n",
    "* **Data Engineering Success:** Handled multi-class low-memory type constraints, mapped scale transformations across heavily contrasting variance categories without target variable leaking, and successfully mapped economic resource management correlations directly into a professional classification report asset."
   ]
  }
 ],
